{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"749a1b65-77dd-44ea-be83-ea9e5678a3da","content":"Here's the recommended setup for all three requirements:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk handles everything:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — no `PackageReference` entries needed. The SDK brings in MSTest, the runner, and CodeCoverage automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add an assembly attribute (e.g., in a `Setup.cs`):\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n`ClassLevel` runs different test classes in parallel (methods within a class remain sequential). Use `ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` if you want full parallelism.\n\n**3. Sequential database tests** — decorate those classes with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void TestDatabaseInsert() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void TestDatabaseQuery() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nClasses marked `[DoNotParallelize]` run alone after all parallel classes finish — no shared-state conflicts.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project file | `MSTest.Sdk` (no explicit packages) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af7d7bd5-dede-4db9-9e45-bd80a762ae05","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no existing codebase. The user is asking for guidance on setting up a new MSTest project. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk, parallel execution, and the `[assembly: DoNotParallelize]` / `[TestClass]` parallelism controls.\n\nLet me give a clear, concise answer with the three things they need:\n\n1. Simplest MSTest.Sdk project file\n2. Parallel by default\n3. Sequential database tests using `[DoNotParallelize]` on specific test classes\n\nMSTest.Sdk is the modern way to set up MSTest projects. \n\nWith MSTest.Sdk, the project file stays minimal since the SDK handles most configuration. Test classes run in parallel by default with MSTest v3+, and I can control this using the `[Parallelize]` assembly attribute to fine-tune worker count and scope, while marking specific test classes with `[DoNotParallelize]` to run them sequentially.","outputTokens":717,"requestId":"E3CE:BC837:1909D41:1C044A8:6A052B72"},"id":"633e2c95-f813-45ad-bc75-c4e1e3db29fd","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:55:15.014Z","parentId":"aac9cbb9-ba08-482c-8f49-75d633da7ce7"}
